      "content": "thanks, that's more like it. i'll look into the custom allocator idea. \n\none more thing, when we were talking about the 'hidden' nature of the leak earlier, you mentioned something about shadows. i'm wondering if there's any specific way to watch for memory being corrupted in the heap that isn't just looking at the total usage? like, how can i tell if a pointer is getting overwritten by something else in a way that's hard to spot?",
